As you may have heard, Google My Maps [0] has recently shut down their Android mobile app. A subset of the functionality has been integrated into the Google Maps app, but it isn&#x27;t possible anymore to edit points and lines on mobile.<p>I used Google My Maps as a way to create and share geological points (POI, markers, pins) on my travel blog:  
- When traveling, I could create points, <i>even while offline</i>, in My Maps  
- An embed My Maps iframe would be dispayed on my website, and friends and family could follow me around<p>Is there any alternative for Android (offline, syncable, iframe-able) that can do this, or any other solution to achieve the above?<p>[0]https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.google.com&#x2F;maps&#x2F;about&#x2F;mymaps&#x2F;
